Persian Gulf Stocks: Kuwait’s Wataniya Telecom and Qatar Cinema

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-08-08T10:44:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/persian-gulf-stocks-kuwait-s-wataniya-telecom-and-qatar-cinema.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  declined
0.8 percent to the lowest since March 17 at the 2 p.m. close in
the emirate. Kuwait Stock Exchange Unweighted Index fell 0.2
percent and Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  decreased 0.8 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.       National Mobile Telecommunications Co. (NMTC KK) advanced
the most since July 21, rising 1 percent to 1,980 fils. The
Kuwaiti phone company controlled by  Qatar Telecom  said second-
quarter profit rose 19 percent to 23.3 million dinars ($85
million) as it added clients.       Qatar Cinema and Film Distribution Co. (QCFS QD) soared as
much as 9.9 percent to 55.7 riyals before closing 0.6 percent
higher. The film importer and movie theater manager said first-
half net income advanced to 4.2 million riyals ($1.15 million)
from 4 million riyals the year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
